(woman humming gentle melody)

01:50.138 --> 01:53.189
♪ ♪

01:59.197 --> 02:01.448
♪ ♪

02:13.320 --> 02:15.545
Miss Rosalee!

02:15.580 --> 02:16.830
Boy, what you doing?

02:16.882 --> 02:18.548
You can't be on this here porch.

02:18.583 --> 02:22.168
I'm sorry, Miss Rosalee,
but it done come early.

02:22.220 --> 02:23.803
Go get my mama from the cookhouse!

02:23.839 --> 02:26.055
♪ ♪

02:45.327 --> 02:49.329
(woman screams)

02:49.364 --> 02:51.030
What happened?!

02:51.032 --> 02:53.449
(screams)

02:53.502 --> 02:55.585
We's was out in the field,

02:55.620 --> 02:56.703
and she just fell holding her stomach.

02:56.755 --> 02:58.121
Shh, you gonna be all right.

02:58.173 --> 02:59.172
Just, just put your leg...

02:59.207 --> 03:00.541
(woman screams)

03:00.566 --> 03:01.624
Should there be that much blood?

03:01.676 --> 03:02.926
(screams)

03:02.961 --> 03:04.460
Come on, come on. Rosalee.

03:05.764 --> 03:08.381
(crying): It hurts.

03:08.383 --> 03:10.600
Zeke, where you keep your clothes?

03:10.635 --> 03:12.385
(woman crying)

03:15.888 --> 03:17.030
Miss Ernestine.

03:17.055 --> 03:19.225
Ain't nothing about
child birth polite, Zeke.

03:19.277 --> 03:20.560
You ain't gonna be no help

03:20.612 --> 03:22.145
if you stand around
slack-jawed at every turn.

03:22.197 --> 03:25.064
Go on outside and wait.

03:25.116 --> 03:27.233
(crying)

03:32.040 --> 03:33.206
It hurts!

03:33.241 --> 03:34.407
(screams)

03:34.409 --> 03:36.576
It's all right.

03:36.578 --> 03:38.453
I know it hurts, but listen to me.

03:38.478 --> 03:40.296
You got to stop pushing.

03:40.332 --> 03:41.331
Mama, what's wrong?

03:41.383 --> 03:42.298
Baby's turned about.

03:42.334 --> 03:43.466
Got to come out head first,

03:43.501 --> 03:44.634
or neither of them gon' make it.

03:44.669 --> 03:45.718
No, no, no, no, no!

03:45.754 --> 03:47.053
Shh!

03:47.088 --> 03:48.388
Put something in her mouth.

03:48.423 --> 03:50.340
No, no, no, no, no, no...

03:50.392 --> 03:52.475
(screams) No, no...

03:52.510 --> 03:54.594
Miss Suzanna gonna throw a fit,

03:54.596 --> 03:56.729
she hear all that noise coming
up at the big house.

03:58.516 --> 04:00.400
- (muffled screaming continues)
- Shh...

04:01.736 --> 04:04.404
(muffled): It hurts, it hurts,
it hurts, it hurts.

04:08.026 --> 04:10.743
(screaming stops)

04:17.118 --> 04:19.752
(baby crying)

04:19.788 --> 04:21.671
It's a boy.

04:23.675 --> 04:25.541
Oh...

04:25.594 --> 04:27.710
(baby crying)

04:33.301 --> 04:35.184
(laughing)

04:35.220 --> 04:37.303
♪ ♪

04:37.305 --> 04:40.640
♪ You're paralyzed ♪

04:40.642 --> 04:43.359
♪ Another dark night ♪

04:43.395 --> 04:47.981
♪ But, oh, I'm not alone... ♪

04:50.535 --> 04:51.818
My name's John Hawkes.

04:51.820 --> 04:53.453
And I stand before you today

04:53.488 --> 04:54.787
because the future of our country

04:54.823 --> 04:57.156
is being decided inside this courtroom.

04:57.158 --> 05:00.493
Dred Scott, by law, is not
allowed a legal defense.

05:00.495 --> 05:03.246
He's not even allowed to defend himself.

05:03.298 --> 05:05.415
So someone should speak for him.

05:05.467 --> 05:08.801
<i>This nation was founded by those fleeing</i>

05:08.837 --> 05:11.804
religious oppression
from across the Atlantic.

05:11.840 --> 05:15.008
Escaping those who would deny
them their freedom.

05:15.010 --> 05:18.478
<i>I ask you, is not the plight</i>

05:18.513 --> 05:20.513
of every runaway slave
but a noble extension

05:20.565 --> 05:23.016
of that same manifest destiny?

05:26.104 --> 05:28.688
(music ends)

05:44.289 --> 05:48.207
There are three legal questions
in front of this court.

05:48.209 --> 05:51.210
The first is about jurisdiction.

05:55.100 --> 05:59.268
MAN: All right, let's,
uh, give it a read.

06:03.391 --> 06:06.059
"Mr. Pullman, thank you
for your prompt payment

06:06.061 --> 06:08.227
"of Charlotte's bills
for the last quarter.

06:08.229 --> 06:10.229
"She's made great steps forward,

06:10.231 --> 06:13.232
"but she takes one or two
backwards from time to time.

06:13.234 --> 06:17.453
"Her latest, injuring one
of our orderlies at lights out.

06:17.489 --> 06:20.740
"We have not included costs
for his medical bills,

06:20.775 --> 06:23.076
"but moving her to a more
secure ward has increased

06:23.078 --> 06:26.129
"the cost of her treatment,
which is at a critical stage.

06:26.164 --> 06:28.464
"We have nothing
but high hopes for her future.

06:28.500 --> 06:30.833
"And you are an important part of that.

06:30.885 --> 06:33.553
Sincerely, Washington Hospital."

06:33.588 --> 06:35.254
I have to say,

06:35.256 --> 06:37.924
it's the third time
they've asked for more money.

06:37.926 --> 06:39.976
Best hospital in the country.

06:43.064 --> 06:44.764
Send one as well.

06:44.816 --> 06:47.266
"Dear Charlotte."

06:50.271 --> 06:52.105
"Hope you are well. Getting well."

06:55.610 --> 06:58.111
"Ben, Jay and I..."

07:02.534 --> 07:03.833
"... we all miss you.

07:03.868 --> 07:05.334
Your loving husband."

07:11.509 --> 07:13.176
<i>(dog barking)</i>

07:13.211 --> 07:15.128
(dogs continue barking)

07:15.180 --> 07:17.296
(bell jingles softly)

07:33.648 --> 07:34.864
August.

07:34.899 --> 07:36.532
MAN: Whoo-wee!

07:36.568 --> 07:38.985
Got us another one, Jim! (laughs)

07:38.987 --> 07:40.403
Saw his bitch with him.

07:40.455 --> 07:41.821
She gonna be close still.

07:41.823 --> 07:43.322
- Eh, we'll get her.
- Yep.

07:43.324 --> 07:44.991
- Hang him up.
- All right.

08:06.431 --> 08:08.681
♪ ♪

08:14.522 --> 08:16.689
(low chatter)

08:17.609 --> 08:19.575
Mama looking for you.

08:19.611 --> 08:20.570
Eat your green beans.

08:20.572 --> 08:21.638
They're ready for the next course.

08:21.663 --> 08:25.081
Liddy, Eve, Rosalee, let's move.

08:25.116 --> 08:27.083
(laughing)

08:27.118 --> 08:30.243
ERNESTINE: Here, let me fix your hair.

08:30.279 --> 08:32.053
I wanted to stay with the baby
till Seraphina woke up.

08:32.106 --> 08:34.841
I covered for you, but there ain't
no excuse for not being here

08:34.876 --> 08:36.542
when dinner's on that table.
And you should know,

08:36.544 --> 08:38.594
there's some trouble going on
with one of the field slaves.

08:38.630 --> 08:41.514
It's got the white folks
on edge, so you mind yourself.

08:41.549 --> 08:44.550
SUZANNA: Why don't we just
invite all the slaves?

08:44.552 --> 08:46.619
Seeing as we're already inviting
everybody else.

08:46.654 --> 08:48.604
MAN: Darling, don't be ridiculous...
we're not inviting everybody.

08:48.640 --> 08:50.523
Just the important bodies.

08:50.558 --> 08:52.058
SUZANNA: Please explain
to me how the Willowsets

08:52.060 --> 08:55.144
are important. Carver
Willowset is about to become

08:55.196 --> 08:56.779
the next bishop of Atlanta.
You can't get elected

08:56.814 --> 08:58.397
in this state without
kissing the lord's ring.

08:58.449 --> 09:00.283
Doesn't anybody care
that this is my birthday.

09:00.318 --> 09:02.401
Not some campaign rally
for Daddy to be mayor.

09:02.403 --> 09:04.036
Senator, sweetie pie.

09:05.240 --> 09:06.706
This has turned into a circus.
I'm exhausted

09:06.741 --> 09:09.242
- just thinking about it.
- Well, the last thing I want

09:09.244 --> 09:12.578
is to exhaust
my beautiful, pregnant wife.

09:12.630 --> 09:15.248
That's why I'm having Avery
send over his house niggers.

09:15.250 --> 09:18.334
As if the slaves can do anything
without my constant instruction.

09:22.090 --> 09:24.090
(exhales)

09:24.092 --> 09:26.425
Can I offer a hand?

09:26.477 --> 09:28.144
Thanks.

09:28.179 --> 09:30.062
No problem.

09:30.098 --> 09:31.430
Mr. Hawkes.

09:31.432 --> 09:33.683
That was a thought-provoking
speech you gave earlier.

09:33.735 --> 09:36.519
Oh. Good to know at least
one person was listening,

09:36.571 --> 09:38.187
- Mister...?
- Still.

09:38.239 --> 09:39.355
William Still.

09:40.441 --> 09:42.191
I've heard of you.

09:42.243 --> 09:43.943
About what you do.

09:43.945 --> 09:45.778
Through discreet circles, I hope.

09:45.780 --> 09:48.281
What I do is why I've sought you
and your horses out this evening.

09:48.333 --> 09:50.616
And are you in need
for a lawyer or a nag?

09:50.668 --> 09:51.867
A home.

09:51.920 --> 09:53.286
Yours, in particular.

09:54.505 --> 09:56.038
(quietly): Its location
along the Ohio River

09:56.090 --> 09:58.341
could be very advantageous to the cause.

09:58.376 --> 10:00.042
Afraid I don't follow.

10:00.094 --> 10:02.128
I believe you do.

10:02.180 --> 10:04.463
You spoke with passion about
the rights of all men today,

10:04.465 --> 10:06.215
but your words fell on deaf ears.

10:06.267 --> 10:08.634
Did that sit well with you? Words aside,

10:08.636 --> 10:10.803
what actions would you be
willing to take to back them up?

10:11.452 --> 10:14.140
I admire what you do, Mr. Still.

10:14.765 --> 10:16.609
And in another life,
I'd like to think that

10:16.644 --> 10:18.239
I could be a man
that would help your cause.

10:18.980 --> 10:20.283
But not in this one?

10:24.202 --> 10:26.652
(horse neighs in distance)

10:35.380 --> 10:37.296
(sighs)

10:41.753 --> 10:43.552
(horse whinnies)

10:43.588 --> 10:45.054
(birds chirping)

10:45.089 --> 10:47.073
About a quarter mile down the road,

10:47.108 --> 10:49.926
you got three slave catchers
making their way towards here.

10:51.512 --> 10:53.646
They got your friend...

10:54.515 --> 10:56.816
... and they got dogs.

11:03.524 --> 11:05.524
Where you headed?

11:09.447 --> 11:10.946
All right, then...

11:10.999 --> 11:12.448
good luck to you.

11:12.500 --> 11:14.750
We's tried following the drinkin' gourd.

11:14.786 --> 11:18.037
You did a fair job at that, but...

11:18.039 --> 11:21.640
you wound up on the wrong side
of the city of Atlanta.

11:27.932 --> 11:29.515
You got two routes north...

11:29.550 --> 11:31.217
Chelsea Savannah and the Ohio River.

11:31.269 --> 11:33.219
This time of year,
your best bet's the Ohio.

11:33.221 --> 11:34.687
She's low and easy to cross.

11:34.722 --> 11:36.222
And when you get there...

11:36.224 --> 11:39.225
there are far more people willing
to help you along the way.

11:39.277 --> 11:41.394
How you know so much?

11:41.446 --> 11:44.230
I made the journey a few times myself.

11:44.282 --> 11:46.866
At night... when the hiding's easier.

11:46.901 --> 11:48.901
Now, you'll have
a straight shot to the river

11:48.903 --> 11:50.569
if you just follow
the Blue Ridge Mountains,

11:50.621 --> 11:52.286
but only way to them is back
through town.

11:52.311 --> 11:54.146
Ain't no way I's gonna make
it without someone seeing me.

11:54.171 --> 11:58.127
- (man whistles)
- (dogs barking, man shouting)

11:58.162 --> 11:59.879
You will if I hide you in the wagon.

11:59.914 --> 12:01.330
Now, I want you to wipe your hands hard

12:01.382 --> 12:04.583
on that tree over there... get all
your sweat and stank off on them.

12:04.635 --> 12:06.919
Then walk your footprints
back into the stream there.

12:06.921 --> 12:08.838
Got to throw off the scent for the dogs.

12:08.890 --> 12:10.806
Make sure you step
in your same footprints.

12:10.842 --> 12:12.141
No new ones.

12:12.176 --> 12:14.810
♪ ♪

12:14.846 --> 12:17.430
(man shouting in distance)

12:19.934 --> 12:21.901
(dogs barking)

12:24.872 --> 12:26.739
(barking continues)

12:26.774 --> 12:28.991
♪ ♪

12:34.582 --> 12:35.865
Search 'em out. Search 'em out.

12:35.917 --> 12:36.949
Good boy! Search 'em out.

12:36.951 --> 12:39.285
She took to the stream!

12:39.337 --> 12:42.371
- PETE: Come on, boys.
- JIM: Hold up.

12:42.423 --> 12:43.756
Hell of a random place

12:43.791 --> 12:46.125
for you to stop to water
your mule, August.

12:46.177 --> 12:48.961
Last place for water till home.

12:50.298 --> 12:52.465
You seen any runaways around here?

12:52.467 --> 12:55.050
You know I wouldn't tell you if I had.

12:55.103 --> 12:57.103
I don't want any trouble.

12:57.138 --> 12:59.738
I'm just gonna be on my way.

13:00.942 --> 13:03.559
Not before I take a look in your wagon.

13:04.729 --> 13:06.028
(yells)

13:07.031 --> 13:08.481
(yells in pain)

13:10.568 --> 13:12.701
You want a hole in you, too, Jim?

13:13.654 --> 13:15.287
(grunts)

13:16.207 --> 13:18.491
♪ It's a long way down ♪

13:18.543 --> 13:19.492
♪ When your head ♪

13:19.494 --> 13:21.877
- ♪ Is in the clouds ♪ - (yells)

13:21.913 --> 13:25.498
- ♪ And all around sirens play ♪
- Over there.

13:25.550 --> 13:28.801
♪ Don't get in my way... ♪

13:28.836 --> 13:30.419
Like I said,

13:30.471 --> 13:34.256
I'll just be on my way.

13:34.308 --> 13:36.509
♪ ♪

13:48.189 --> 13:49.939
JOHN: <i>Elizabeth?</i>

13:49.991 --> 13:52.107
(distant banging, crashing)

13:54.946 --> 13:56.274
Elizabeth?

13:57.608 --> 13:58.809
Elizabeth.

14:04.372 --> 14:05.454
(grunts)

14:05.506 --> 14:06.872
John.

14:06.924 --> 14:08.841
(chuckles) You're home early.

14:08.876 --> 14:10.509
I thought you're not due to arrive
until just before the train.

14:10.545 --> 14:14.065
Would the house
still be standing if I had?

14:15.466 --> 14:18.100
(chuckles) Mmm.

14:18.135 --> 14:21.520
Now, I know this all looks unpleasant,

14:21.556 --> 14:23.472
Oh. but once my intentions for
the space are fully realized...

14:23.524 --> 14:25.724
You see, I woke up this morning,
and I thought

14:25.726 --> 14:27.226
the baby should have light.

14:27.278 --> 14:28.644
More light than it could stand.
And I came

14:28.696 --> 14:31.363
to the conclusion the nursery
should have French doors.

14:32.233 --> 14:34.316
French doors? And... Yeah.

14:34.368 --> 14:36.368
over there? Is a... veranda?

14:36.404 --> 14:38.871
No. That was an unfortunate mishap.

14:38.906 --> 14:40.623
(shouts)

14:40.658 --> 14:42.908
(grunting)

14:42.910 --> 14:45.244
The sledgehammer is quite heavy.

14:45.246 --> 14:47.129
What do you think about curtains?

14:47.164 --> 14:48.714
I think they should cover the windows,

14:48.749 --> 14:49.915
- keep the light out.
- You're a tease.

14:49.917 --> 14:51.383
I meant colors. Of course,

14:51.419 --> 14:53.302
it's difficult to decide
without knowing if it's gonna be

14:53.337 --> 14:54.887
a boy or a girl, so I was thinking

14:54.922 --> 14:57.256
maybe yellow.

14:57.308 --> 14:59.258
MAN: <i>It's not that uncommon.</i>

14:59.310 --> 15:01.227
There's nothing to be ashamed of.

15:01.262 --> 15:04.263
The human body is like
a garden, and some gardens,

15:04.315 --> 15:06.765
<i>unfortunately, well,
they lack a certain...</i>

15:06.767 --> 15:09.018
(no audio)

15:12.406 --> 15:14.523
Yellow's a lovely color.

15:16.360 --> 15:18.193
(exhales)

15:18.246 --> 15:20.112
Tell me how your trip went.

15:21.282 --> 15:22.948
It was great. It was, uh... it was good.

15:23.000 --> 15:24.283
People were listening.

15:24.285 --> 15:26.368
Just not the right people.

15:26.420 --> 15:28.787
I've heard the case is not
likely to go Mr. Scott's way.

15:28.789 --> 15:30.422
He did everything right. He followed

15:30.458 --> 15:33.759
the law to the letter, yet he
still finds himself in chains.

15:33.794 --> 15:37.752
What's a man supposed to do
when he feels so powerless?

15:38.966 --> 15:40.408
Well...

15:40.885 --> 15:44.436
I don't pretend to know anything
about the ways of men.

15:44.472 --> 15:46.772
But as a dainty little lady like me,

15:46.807 --> 15:49.608
why, I pick up a sledgehammer...

15:49.644 --> 15:53.864
(grunts) pray for the best,
and hope that God is listening.

15:57.818 --> 15:59.985
(chuckles)

16:00.988 --> 16:03.789
HAROLD: Let's go! Move!

16:03.824 --> 16:05.958
Get!

16:06.627 --> 16:09.411
(shivering)

16:09.463 --> 16:10.829
HAROLD: Go! Move!

16:10.881 --> 16:12.298
Let's go, let's go.

16:12.333 --> 16:14.967
- Move it.
- Settle in. You'll be going

16:15.002 --> 16:16.635
back to your masters soon.

16:16.671 --> 16:18.053
Now y'all stay put

16:18.089 --> 16:21.340
and stay quiet!

16:21.392 --> 16:23.175
Come on, Jim.

16:30.067 --> 16:32.184
(locks, latches clicking)

16:46.083 --> 16:49.535
(shuddering breaths)

16:49.587 --> 16:51.203
(coughing)

17:17.865 --> 17:19.982
Miss Suzanna wants her bath early.

17:20.034 --> 17:22.178
You gonna have to take
James out to your brother.

17:22.953 --> 17:25.654
And when you get back, warm
up some milk for Miss Mary.

17:27.157 --> 17:29.291
(crickets chirping)

17:33.414 --> 17:35.241
You can let go of me now.

17:36.751 --> 17:38.834
(chattering indistinctly)

17:44.675 --> 17:48.177
(owl hooting)

17:48.229 --> 17:49.478
Miss Rosalee,

17:49.513 --> 17:51.680
we don't get to see your pretty
face enough around here.

17:51.732 --> 17:52.598
Pearly Mae,

17:53.518 --> 17:56.344
it's time for our evening prayers.

18:09.033 --> 18:11.116
(humming softly)

18:14.872 --> 18:16.672
Is that for me, Sam? (chuckles)

18:16.707 --> 18:18.039
When it's finished.

18:18.091 --> 18:19.958
Wait till T.R. sees it.

18:19.960 --> 18:21.543
Listen now,

18:21.595 --> 18:23.128
this ain't for playin' with
in no big house.

18:23.180 --> 18:25.347
It stays here or you can't
have it, you hear me?

18:26.801 --> 18:27.966
Hand-carved like that.

18:28.018 --> 18:30.519
Better than any of them toys T.R. has.

18:30.554 --> 18:31.770
Mama sent some dinner.

18:31.806 --> 18:34.473
Mm-hmm. Scraps off of massa's table.

18:34.525 --> 18:37.059
It might be good enough for you,
but I ain't no dog.

18:37.111 --> 18:40.028
(shouting)

18:40.064 --> 18:42.648
MAN: Get on in the house! Where is he?

18:42.650 --> 18:45.317
Why they hurtin' Henry?

18:45.319 --> 18:47.119
They been askin' about Noah.

18:47.154 --> 18:49.154
Massa sent him on some work
down the way, was due back

18:49.206 --> 18:50.823
(blows landing) this morning.

18:58.438 --> 18:59.748
How'd they get you?

18:59.800 --> 19:01.917
(men talking in distance)

19:01.969 --> 19:04.052
I wasn't runnin'.

19:04.910 --> 19:06.755
Yet here you are.

19:06.807 --> 19:10.092
They sicced them dogs on me
before I could show 'em my pass.

19:11.011 --> 19:13.566
You might've fooled them,

19:14.315 --> 19:16.932
but I can see that fire
you trying to snuff out.

19:19.494 --> 19:21.507
Freedom burning behind those eyes.

19:24.247 --> 19:25.825
You want to know something?

19:27.327 --> 19:28.695
I made it.

19:29.319 --> 19:31.790
I made it to that river.

19:32.733 --> 19:35.200
Came out a free man.

19:38.205 --> 19:39.503
Until...

19:40.040 --> 19:42.207
(grunting, gasping)

19:45.819 --> 19:46.870
I had it.

19:48.182 --> 19:49.644
The map to freedom.

19:51.218 --> 19:53.866
Ain't no such thing as a map to freedom.

19:54.221 --> 19:56.188
Word for word,

19:56.223 --> 19:58.023
it showed me the way.

20:01.428 --> 20:03.729
I carved it out on the wall.

20:05.900 --> 20:08.033
(grunting)

20:10.571 --> 20:12.037
You ought to rest now.

20:12.957 --> 20:15.324
You listen to me.

20:15.376 --> 20:17.409
You got to have faith.

20:17.411 --> 20:20.295
You run...

20:20.331 --> 20:23.298
you follow that map,

20:23.334 --> 20:25.584
and you a free man.

20:27.671 --> 20:30.364
I seen the devil's grin,

20:31.976 --> 20:34.300
but I missed the angel's light.

20:37.348 --> 20:39.862
You be ready when you get to that river.

21:18.055 --> 21:21.106
(grunting)

21:33.704 --> 21:35.821
(woman muttering, crying)

21:41.412 --> 21:43.116
Seraphina?

21:44.465 --> 21:46.715
Seraphina. Come on now.

21:46.750 --> 21:48.667
You should be restin'. Let's go.
I washed him clean

21:48.669 --> 21:51.503
of the sins of this life. Of the pain.

21:51.505 --> 21:53.839
I couldn't have him
growin' up like this.

21:53.891 --> 21:55.641
Oh, not like this.

21:55.676 --> 21:57.893
And he free now.

21:57.928 --> 22:00.262
(gasping)

22:01.382 --> 22:02.881
(panting)

22:02.916 --> 22:04.516
(gasping)

22:04.518 --> 22:07.352
(panting)

22:11.275 --> 22:12.524
(screams)

22:13.527 --> 22:17.863
(crying)

22:24.304 --> 22:26.455
(birds chirping)

22:46.527 --> 22:48.143
I can guess where your head's at,

22:48.195 --> 22:49.861
but you got to bring it back here.

22:49.897 --> 22:51.196
Right here on these cakes,

22:51.231 --> 22:53.865
'cause we using all the eggs we got.

22:56.704 --> 22:58.904
I just can't understand

22:58.906 --> 23:01.406
how someone could do that
to their own baby.

23:01.458 --> 23:03.041
I can.

23:03.536 --> 23:05.327
Fear is something powerful.

23:05.379 --> 23:07.546
From a young age, we think we know it.

23:07.581 --> 23:09.798
But I ain't never truly felt fear,

23:09.833 --> 23:12.801
real fear, until I had you
and your brothers.

23:14.116 --> 23:15.921
From the minute y'all were born,

23:15.973 --> 23:17.255
I was afraid of losing you.

23:17.307 --> 23:19.558
That y'all be sold or kilt.

23:19.593 --> 23:22.811
That your brothers would be
worked and beat to the bone.

23:22.846 --> 23:24.598
And that you'd be too purty.

23:26.375 --> 23:29.454
There ain't no fear like
that you have for your child.

23:30.020 --> 23:32.073
Make it so you can't see straight.

23:33.323 --> 23:36.024
You can't change
what you saw last night.

23:36.486 --> 23:38.133
Focus on what's in front of you.

23:38.612 --> 23:40.320
Lose yourself in the work.

23:41.949 --> 23:44.833
(exhales)

23:50.207 --> 23:52.124
(sizzling)

23:52.126 --> 23:53.925
Stand up.

24:02.686 --> 24:03.935
I put my trust in you, Noah.

24:03.971 --> 24:05.437
You were supposed to take that wagon

24:05.472 --> 24:07.022
to the Ludlow plantation,
drop off that anvil,

24:07.057 --> 24:08.273
come right on back.

24:08.308 --> 24:10.308
I sorry, massa.
That's what I intended to do.

24:10.360 --> 24:12.694
Don't lie to me, Noah.
They said they found you

24:12.729 --> 24:15.063
outside of Atlanta.
That's two counties over.

24:15.115 --> 24:16.314
Yes, massa, I got lost.

24:16.316 --> 24:18.066
Bullshit.

24:18.118 --> 24:19.151
Yo' ass was runnin'.

24:19.203 --> 24:20.235
No, no, massa, massa,

24:20.287 --> 24:21.987
it was dark and I was scared

24:21.989 --> 24:23.989
and they sicced them dogs on me
before I could show 'em my pass.

24:24.041 --> 24:25.123
You wasn't lost!

24:25.159 --> 24:26.208
- I was lost.
- You made that trip

24:26.243 --> 24:27.542
six times now.

24:27.578 --> 24:28.743
And I always come back.

24:28.796 --> 24:30.212
I always come back, massa.

24:30.247 --> 24:32.080
(crying): I always come back.

24:32.132 --> 24:37.002
I'm sorry, massa. I swear. I swear.

24:37.054 --> 24:38.970
Bill,

24:39.006 --> 24:41.890
how many miles you reckon
between my plantation

24:41.925 --> 24:44.059
- and the North?
- Hell,

24:44.094 --> 24:45.177
more than I can count.

24:45.229 --> 24:47.179
Well, my guess, at least 600.

24:47.181 --> 24:51.016
On foot, there is not a man
on earth who could make that.

24:51.068 --> 24:53.819
Especially not being hunted
by those whose sole aim

24:53.854 --> 24:57.189
is to drag him back in chains,
dead or alive. Add to that,

24:57.241 --> 24:58.690
there isn't anywhere to hide

24:58.742 --> 25:01.276
as a nigger in a white man's
world, and you got yourself

25:01.328 --> 25:02.526
an impossible feat.

25:03.306 --> 25:07.032
Almost as impossible
as getting off my plantation.

25:07.034 --> 25:08.834
Got the Yellow River on one side,

25:08.869 --> 25:10.535
Stone Mountain the other.

25:10.587 --> 25:15.257
300 acres of thicket
and swamp everywhere else.

25:15.292 --> 25:17.959
I do, I swear, on the fourth day,

25:18.011 --> 25:20.378
the Lord our God blessed me

25:20.380 --> 25:22.173
with a fortress.

25:23.383 --> 25:27.969
20 years I've been the master
of this plantation,

25:29.330 --> 25:31.306
and I have not had

25:31.358 --> 25:32.998
one runaway.

25:33.861 --> 25:35.416
Not one.

25:35.896 --> 25:37.529
(panting)

25:39.283 --> 25:41.045
And he ain't the first.

25:43.305 --> 25:46.071
Only takes one bad nigger
to spoil 'em all.

25:46.073 --> 25:47.789
He can barely stand.
He ain't runnin' any time soon.

25:47.824 --> 25:48.957
You and Bill

25:48.992 --> 25:50.298
keep an eye on him all the same.

25:51.024 --> 25:53.579
I'm gonna send someone down here
to tend to that leg.

25:53.580 --> 25:55.213
And then you get back in that shop.

25:55.249 --> 25:56.498
There's still work to be done today.

25:57.420 --> 25:59.417
- Thank you, massa.
- Oh.

26:00.129 --> 26:03.805
I had to pay those
slave catchers five dollars

26:03.840 --> 26:05.807
because of your terrible sense
of direction.

26:05.842 --> 26:08.977
A lash for each dollar seems fair.

26:28.165 --> 26:32.534
Whoa. Whoa, mule. Whoa, mule.

26:32.586 --> 26:35.170
(grunting)

26:35.205 --> 26:37.088
We've made it
to the other side of the city.

26:37.124 --> 26:38.623
It's safe to get out now.

26:48.969 --> 26:51.303
Why you do this?

26:52.222 --> 26:53.582
Help people like me.

26:56.944 --> 26:58.485
I got a boy.

26:59.313 --> 27:00.958
Name is Ben.

27:01.398 --> 27:03.531
Coming up on 12 years old.

27:03.567 --> 27:05.650
He don't yet know the world's

27:05.652 --> 27:07.670
a harsh and unfair place.

27:09.790 --> 27:12.127
And I'm afraid there
ain't no changin' that.

27:12.576 --> 27:14.031
Not in my life, anyway.

27:14.328 --> 27:15.660
So, I suppose

27:15.662 --> 27:19.414
when it comes down to it, I'm just...

27:19.466 --> 27:22.000
thinking of his future.

27:24.222 --> 27:25.342
Thank you.

27:25.839 --> 27:28.056
♪ ♪

27:32.929 --> 27:34.729
(horse huffs)

27:37.818 --> 27:40.029
Get up, so she can look at that leg.

28:06.797 --> 28:09.381
You gonna have to take off your shirt.

28:10.767 --> 28:13.018
(gasping in pain)

28:13.053 --> 28:16.271
Seems I... I need some help,

28:16.306 --> 28:17.795
if you don't mind.

28:20.610 --> 28:22.861
(horse neighs in distance)

28:28.035 --> 28:30.235
(panting quietly)

28:31.154 --> 28:33.222
It's Rose, right?

28:34.991 --> 28:36.991
Ro-Rosalee.

28:37.044 --> 28:38.827
I'm Noah.

28:38.879 --> 28:40.124
I know your brother.

28:40.580 --> 28:42.997
I don't think <i> we</i> ever spoke before.

28:43.050 --> 28:45.443
You don't leave the big house much.

28:45.752 --> 28:47.085
(gasps quietly)

28:47.087 --> 28:50.088
I always wonder what
it must be like up there,

28:50.090 --> 28:52.390
sleeping in them nice comfy beds.

28:52.426 --> 28:54.426
(trembling breath)

28:54.428 --> 28:57.512
We still slaves... don't
matter where you sleep.

28:57.564 --> 28:59.097
(exhales)

28:59.099 --> 29:00.815
(shudders)

29:00.851 --> 29:02.484
(gasping breath)

29:06.773 --> 29:09.240
- This ain't that bad.
- It ain't?

29:11.695 --> 29:14.362
Then hell, I guess I should
put this to better use.

29:14.414 --> 29:17.615
♪ ♪

29:19.870 --> 29:21.454
Why is you's pretending?

29:22.372 --> 29:24.923
We all pretendin' in some way.

29:24.958 --> 29:26.958
It's nice to meet you properly,

29:27.010 --> 29:28.960
Miss Rose.

29:35.302 --> 29:37.552
♪ ♪

29:45.362 --> 29:47.479
(train whistle blows)

29:47.481 --> 29:48.646
(panting)

29:48.698 --> 29:50.281
(train whistle blows)

29:53.453 --> 29:55.453
(moaning, panting)

29:55.489 --> 29:57.322
- (grunting)
- Wait. Wait, hold it.

29:57.374 --> 30:00.575
No, wait. Laney Briss told me if you
put a pillow under my bottom...

30:00.627 --> 30:02.710
Wait, you're talking
to your friends about this?

30:02.746 --> 30:04.913
(panting): Which amendment is it?

30:04.965 --> 30:07.332
The one which prevents
incriminating oneself?

30:07.334 --> 30:08.800
- (laughs)
- (grunts)

30:08.835 --> 30:10.218
Wait, wait, wait.

30:10.253 --> 30:11.419
(exhales)

30:11.471 --> 30:13.588
(exhales)

30:13.640 --> 30:15.924
I'm sorry.

30:15.976 --> 30:17.592
(exhales)

30:17.644 --> 30:20.595
I can't seem to get out of my own head.

30:20.647 --> 30:22.013
Oh, don't apologize.

30:22.065 --> 30:23.815
You're not the only one.

30:23.850 --> 30:26.351
(train wheels clacking)

30:27.487 --> 30:29.187
A man came to see me at the capital.

30:29.239 --> 30:31.940
- Mm-hmm?
- A William Still. Pennsylvania.

30:32.825 --> 30:35.276
The one that aids the runaway slaves?

30:35.328 --> 30:36.744
He asked about using our house.

30:36.780 --> 30:38.363
To do what?

30:39.451 --> 30:41.032
To... help people.

30:41.084 --> 30:43.701
You mean to harbor fugitives?

30:43.703 --> 30:46.538
I mean both, I suppose.

30:46.590 --> 30:47.839
I told him that...

30:47.874 --> 30:50.175
we couldn't be of any help to him.

30:52.095 --> 30:53.878
But what if we did?

30:53.880 --> 30:55.430
We could make

30:55.465 --> 30:56.881
a real difference.

30:56.933 --> 30:58.716
Well, it's a n-noble cause

30:58.718 --> 31:01.279
and... somebody has to do it.

31:03.273 --> 31:05.223
But it doesn't have to be us.

31:06.142 --> 31:08.443
We could be thrown in jail.

31:08.478 --> 31:10.195
You <i> know</i> it's breaking the law.

31:10.230 --> 31:11.946
Yeah, that same law allows people

31:11.982 --> 31:13.423
to own other people.

31:13.733 --> 31:16.868
It's not enough for me to just
speak about this anymore,

31:16.903 --> 31:18.369
- Elizabeth...
- But-but you're talking

31:18.405 --> 31:20.738
- about risking our future.
- Risk?

31:20.740 --> 31:23.374
Most runaways are
either recaptured or killed.

31:23.410 --> 31:25.577
- I've heard horrible things.
- Yeah, as have I,

31:25.579 --> 31:27.078
from my friends, about angry Negroes

31:27.130 --> 31:29.047
who kill the owners of safe houses

31:29.082 --> 31:31.234
and then make away
with their possessions.

31:31.918 --> 31:33.251
What if...

31:33.769 --> 31:36.422
on our way back
we stop over in Pennsylvania

31:36.423 --> 31:38.840
- and we just hear what he has to say.
- Absolutely not.

31:38.892 --> 31:40.258
- Wh-Why?
- Absolutely not.

31:40.310 --> 31:42.927
This is our home, and you need
to think about our family.

31:42.979 --> 31:44.429
What family, Elizabeth?

31:46.516 --> 31:48.316
(exhales)

31:48.351 --> 31:50.435
(train whistle blowing)

31:54.491 --> 31:56.608
(crickets chirping)

32:00.030 --> 32:01.779
(panting)

32:01.831 --> 32:03.164
How many?

32:03.199 --> 32:05.283
200. Every night.

32:05.335 --> 32:07.452
600 since you left.

32:07.454 --> 32:08.620
Add 50 more.

32:09.789 --> 32:11.122
You said you'd be back before they knew

32:11.124 --> 32:13.758
you's was gone. I ran into some trouble.

32:13.793 --> 32:15.843
I didn't make it to the city
like I planned.

32:15.879 --> 32:17.512
Come here. You all right?

32:17.547 --> 32:18.763
Good.

32:18.798 --> 32:21.015
- What about you? That limp.
- Oh, I got

32:21.051 --> 32:23.301
to let them think I'm weak,
that I ain't no threat.

32:23.353 --> 32:25.970
So they can stop watching me so close.

32:29.643 --> 32:31.643
(panting)

32:31.695 --> 32:33.778
I think I found it.

32:34.881 --> 32:36.614
The way to the promised land.

32:36.650 --> 32:38.316
Look.

32:41.621 --> 32:44.989
Now, this here, this was carved
on the jailhouse wall.

32:45.041 --> 32:46.491
Now, I don't know much,

32:46.543 --> 32:49.627
but I know that there says "freedom."

32:49.663 --> 32:51.996
We gots to find somebody
to read this to us.

32:52.048 --> 32:54.048
No, we got to do way more than that.

32:54.084 --> 32:56.167
That jailhouse was filled
with poor souls

32:56.169 --> 32:57.752
being dragged back in chains.

32:57.804 --> 32:59.721
You know what they all had in common?

32:59.756 --> 33:01.673
They was all alone.

33:01.725 --> 33:04.642
It ain't enough
to just find which way to go...

33:04.678 --> 33:06.311
we got to get a group of us together.

33:06.346 --> 33:07.729
- Yeah.
- Be clever about it.

33:07.764 --> 33:09.647
Find a strength in numbers,
'cause, look, when we run...

33:09.683 --> 33:10.948
when we run...

33:10.984 --> 33:15.186
ain't no white man
gonna be able to stop us.

33:18.024 --> 33:20.692
MARY: Daddy, you like my hair?

33:20.744 --> 33:22.827
It's beautiful, sweetie pie.

33:22.862 --> 33:24.829
There. All done.

33:24.864 --> 33:27.498
We'll pull the back out
right before the party.

33:27.534 --> 33:31.035
All curled up, you look like a
princess in them picture books.

33:31.087 --> 33:33.004
My hair, my dress, my party...

33:33.039 --> 33:34.789
everything's gonna be perfect.

33:34.841 --> 33:35.873
And it's all

33:35.925 --> 33:38.126
- thanks to you, Stine.
- (Ernestine chuckles)

33:39.963 --> 33:42.630
James is sure getting big these days.

33:42.682 --> 33:44.632
How old is he now, eight?

33:44.684 --> 33:46.718
- Gonna be seven this year.
- We get him

33:46.770 --> 33:48.636
out in that field, get him strong,

33:48.688 --> 33:51.723
I'll bet he'd fetch us
a good price on the block.

33:51.775 --> 33:53.859
What do you say to that, Tom?

33:53.894 --> 33:55.893
Finally make some money
off one of these niggers.

33:55.945 --> 33:57.362
TOM: Mm.

33:57.397 --> 33:59.897
♪ ♪

33:59.949 --> 34:02.316
NOAH: Paddy rollers always move in twos.

34:02.369 --> 34:04.452
There were three of them
catchers that got me.

34:04.487 --> 34:07.321
Means we need at least two
more on the run with us.

34:07.374 --> 34:10.074
HENRY: Seems like more people
are just gonna slow us down.

34:10.076 --> 34:11.492
No, it ain't about speed.

34:11.543 --> 34:13.710
We ain't gonna get off
this plantation by just running,

34:13.746 --> 34:16.547
and we ain't gonna get
600 miles north without help.

34:16.583 --> 34:17.998
So who you thinkin'?

34:18.051 --> 34:19.500
Moses.

34:19.552 --> 34:20.835
HENRY: The preacher man?

34:20.887 --> 34:22.503
The one that's saying every Sunday that

34:22.554 --> 34:24.472
- God said to obey thy massa?
- You said it yourself,

34:24.507 --> 34:26.007
we need somebody who can read.

34:26.059 --> 34:28.643
<i>You see how that holy spirit
catch him on Sunday.</i>

34:28.678 --> 34:30.428
<i>Them words ain't comin' from God.</i>

34:30.429 --> 34:33.648
<i>They comin' from that book
he keep hidin'.</i>

34:33.683 --> 34:36.484
I guess having God on our side
wouldn't hurt none, neither.

34:36.518 --> 34:38.402
Oh, if he's picked a side,

34:38.438 --> 34:40.353
it ain't ours.

34:41.274 --> 34:42.774
How about Sam?

34:42.826 --> 34:44.492
He's smart.

34:44.527 --> 34:47.495
Clever building things;
he could come in handy.

34:47.530 --> 34:50.614
NOAH: <i>No, he save up what little
they give him in the shop.</i>

34:50.667 --> 34:53.951
<i>Fool thinks the massa gonna
let him buy his freedom.</i>

34:55.422 --> 34:59.457
He play by the rules...
might not be able to trust him.

34:59.459 --> 35:01.709
Nah, we go for Zeke.

35:01.761 --> 35:03.461
He big as a house.

35:03.463 --> 35:05.012
HENRY: I once saw him

35:05.048 --> 35:07.632
<i>near kill a man who tried
to have his way with Seraphina.</i>

35:07.634 --> 35:09.801
<i>He'd destroy anything in our way.</i>

35:12.105 --> 35:14.138
NOAH: Now he ain't got nothin' left,

35:14.190 --> 35:16.474
save for a wife who killed his baby.

35:16.526 --> 35:17.892
Everybody be paying
their respects tonight

35:17.944 --> 35:19.694
when they put that baby in the ground.

35:19.729 --> 35:22.113
- That's gonna be our only chance...
- How's that leg?

35:22.148 --> 35:24.315
It's doing all right, Mr. Cato.
I appreciate you asking.

35:24.367 --> 35:27.368
They find your wagon, they know
you ain't been to the Ludlow's.

35:27.403 --> 35:29.370
Know you was on
the wrong side of Atlanta.

35:29.405 --> 35:31.405
It ain't <i> my</i> wagon, it's the massa's.

35:31.458 --> 35:33.324
It's been out there for days.

35:33.326 --> 35:36.661
All them bandits... you really think
there's anything left to find?

35:36.713 --> 35:37.795
You think you smart, huh?

35:37.831 --> 35:38.963
No, sir. "No, sir."

35:38.998 --> 35:39.997
Please, massa, please,

35:39.999 --> 35:41.749
I just a big ol' dumb nigger.

35:41.801 --> 35:43.468
Please don't punish me!

35:44.587 --> 35:46.504
You might've fooled them, but I see you.

35:46.556 --> 35:48.890
You a troublemaker,
and you got the itch.

35:48.925 --> 35:50.308
That about right, ain't it?

35:50.343 --> 35:52.477
You think you smarter
than the rest of us.

35:52.512 --> 35:54.645
You think you a free man.

35:55.899 --> 35:58.516
You have yourself a nice day,
now, Mr. Cato.

35:58.568 --> 36:00.985
Well, you ain't as smart as you think,
so I'm-a give you some advice, boy!

36:01.020 --> 36:04.021
Don't you play big nigger with me!

36:05.074 --> 36:08.359
(chuckles softly)

36:08.411 --> 36:11.162
Y'all have a nice day, now.

36:13.032 --> 36:15.700
I'll keep my eye out for that wagon.

36:18.371 --> 36:20.004
We got to do this right,

36:20.039 --> 36:23.424
or we's dead before we step
one foot off this plantation.

36:24.344 --> 36:27.445
(horse neighing excitedly)

36:28.681 --> 36:30.348
(neighs)

36:30.383 --> 36:32.884
Best keep her away.

36:32.886 --> 36:34.685
For her own good.

36:34.721 --> 36:36.521
They all gone sick, Pa.

36:36.556 --> 36:38.105
What is it?

36:38.141 --> 36:40.558
Milk poison, best I could tell.

36:40.610 --> 36:43.728
(horse's sickly neighing)

36:48.985 --> 36:51.319
What are y'all gonna do?

36:51.371 --> 36:53.571
(horse's sickly neighing)

36:53.573 --> 36:55.790
Do you know what? Come here.

36:57.010 --> 36:58.576
You know, I almost forgot...

36:58.628 --> 37:01.128
I got you something from up north.

37:03.583 --> 37:05.049
What is it?

37:05.084 --> 37:07.134
That there is called a "baseball."

37:07.170 --> 37:09.887
Whole new sport was invented
a couple of years back.

37:09.923 --> 37:13.224
Some regulars in a Yankee tavern
were going on about it. And this...

37:13.259 --> 37:15.009
is for catching the ball.

37:15.061 --> 37:17.428
Go ahead, put your hand
in there. Like that.

37:17.480 --> 37:20.097
You know how we got to break
this leather in, right?

37:20.149 --> 37:22.483
Like on a saddle?
So that it works right.

37:22.518 --> 37:25.736
Some fella in the tavern
was suggesting that you tuck

37:25.772 --> 37:28.739
the ball on in there so that they get
to know each other a little better.

37:28.775 --> 37:31.442
Why don't you go up to the house
and do that now, Ben, hmm?

37:35.882 --> 37:38.282
(horse's sickly neighing)

37:43.206 --> 37:45.339
(hammering nearby)

37:51.848 --> 37:53.514
Sam. Sam.

37:54.684 --> 37:57.969
Tonight at the funeral, we need to talk.

38:08.114 --> 38:10.815
(neighing)

38:13.620 --> 38:16.120
(grunts, groans)

38:16.155 --> 38:18.956
Aw, damn it!

38:20.126 --> 38:21.158
You see what you done?!

38:21.194 --> 38:23.094
Rosalee, go down there

38:23.129 --> 38:24.762
and tell my son to come inside.

38:24.797 --> 38:28.299
- I'll go, Miss Suzanna.
- Quickly now, Rosalee.

38:29.385 --> 38:32.253
BILL: Look what you done!

38:32.305 --> 38:35.640
♪ ♪

38:35.675 --> 38:37.725
You got 'em all dirty!

38:37.760 --> 38:39.510
Them things worth more than

38:39.512 --> 38:41.345
- your life, boy!
- M-Mr. Bill?

38:41.347 --> 38:42.813
Get your hands out.

38:42.849 --> 38:45.232
- Put 'em out!
- M-Mr. Bill, uh, Miss Suzanna

38:45.268 --> 38:47.151
wants, uh, Mr. T.R.

38:47.186 --> 38:49.353
and James to go back up
on that porch with her.

38:49.355 --> 38:50.905
This boy's gonna pay
for wasting my time.

38:50.940 --> 38:51.939
Hold 'em out!

38:51.991 --> 38:55.276
(James crying quietly)

38:56.195 --> 38:58.612
It's my fault.

38:58.665 --> 39:01.082
It's my fault, Mr. Bill, it's my fault.

39:01.117 --> 39:04.335
I gave 'em the sugar...
that's got 'em running wild.

39:04.370 --> 39:08.039
If anybody gonna be punished,
it's gonna be me.

39:08.041 --> 39:09.540
(crying): Please...

39:09.542 --> 39:12.593
So that's how they do it up
in the big house, is it?

39:12.628 --> 39:14.428
You just talk to me

39:14.464 --> 39:16.297
- any way you want?
- N-No, sir.

39:16.349 --> 39:18.033
Come down here and tell me how
it's gonna be?!

39:18.058 --> 39:18.849
No, no, sir.

39:18.885 --> 39:21.052
He a little boy, sir. He's a little boy.

39:21.721 --> 39:22.887
(yells)

39:22.889 --> 39:24.055
(shudders)

39:24.724 --> 39:27.475
(gasps, cries)

39:27.527 --> 39:28.943
(gasps)

39:28.978 --> 39:31.979
(Rosalee crying)

39:32.031 --> 39:34.148
(whip strikes, Rosalee gasps)

39:34.200 --> 39:35.816
(sobbing)

39:42.158 --> 39:43.991
- (whip strikes)
- (gasps)

39:44.043 --> 39:46.494
♪
♪ (sobbing)

39:46.546 --> 39:48.379
(whip strikes, Rosalee gasps)

39:48.414 --> 39:50.798
- ♪
♪ - (whip cracks)

39:52.418 --> 39:54.668
- ♪
♪ - (muted)

40:01.728 --> 40:03.010
Massa?

40:03.062 --> 40:04.845
Guests are coming up the drive.

40:04.897 --> 40:06.814
(whip strikes, Rosalee gasps)

40:11.237 --> 40:12.520
Bill!

40:12.572 --> 40:14.438
That's enough.
She's gonna need those hands

40:14.490 --> 40:16.607
to serve at the party tonight.

40:19.996 --> 40:22.113
(crying)

40:51.644 --> 40:53.027
(sighs)

40:55.148 --> 40:57.148
Can the handsome devil
standing before me

40:57.150 --> 40:59.033
really be my brother?

40:59.068 --> 41:01.202
(grunts) Hey, Tom.

41:01.237 --> 41:03.404
It's been too long.

41:03.456 --> 41:04.789
Lizzy.

41:04.824 --> 41:05.990
Mmm.

41:05.992 --> 41:09.043
What have you been feeding him?

41:11.430 --> 41:17.568
♪ I got a robe... ♪

41:18.404 --> 41:26.427
♪ You got a robe... ♪

41:26.479 --> 41:29.847
ALL: ♪ All God's children got ♪

41:29.849 --> 41:33.434
♪ A robe ♪

41:33.486 --> 41:37.230
♪ When I get to heaven, gonna ♪

41:37.265 --> 41:40.124
♪ Put on my robe ♪

41:40.159 --> 41:43.236
♪ Shout all over God's ♪

41:43.261 --> 41:49.416
♪ Heaven, heaven ♪

41:49.452 --> 41:53.504
♪ Heaven ♪

41:53.539 --> 41:56.303
♪ I got wings ♪

41:56.355 --> 41:58.978
♪ You got wings ♪

41:59.003 --> 42:04.014
ALL: ♪ All God's children got wings ♪

42:04.050 --> 42:09.220
♪ When I get to heaven,
gonna put on my wings ♪

42:09.272 --> 42:14.536
♪ I'm gonna fly all over God's heaven ♪

42:14.589 --> 42:18.028
♪ Everybody talkin' 'bout heaven ♪

42:18.064 --> 42:20.064
♪ Ain't goin' there ♪

42:20.066 --> 42:24.702
♪ Heaven, heaven ♪

42:24.737 --> 42:32.076
♪ I'm gonna fly all over God's heaven. ♪

42:32.078 --> 42:34.545
♪ ♪

42:34.580 --> 42:37.478
♪ Oh, oh, la, oh, la, la mar ♪

42:37.480 --> 42:39.967
♪ Que bonita ola ♪

42:40.002 --> 42:41.969
♪ Para navegar, I got those icies ♪

42:42.004 --> 42:44.388
♪ I got that zoom, zoom,
you want to wife me ♪

42:44.423 --> 42:47.558
♪ I know you do,
I'm on that gravy train ♪

42:47.593 --> 42:49.009
♪ I bet you're making waves ♪

42:49.061 --> 42:50.644
♪ Got too much cash flow ♪

42:50.680 --> 42:52.229
♪ I'm pouring money down the drain ♪

42:52.265 --> 42:55.266
♪ Oh, oh, la, oh, la, la mar... ♪

42:55.268 --> 42:57.434
♪ Heaven, I'm gonna ♪

42:57.436 --> 43:01.272
♪ Play all over God's heaven. ♪

43:01.324 --> 43:04.942
(music fades, indistinct chatter)

43:04.944 --> 43:06.110
(grunting)

43:06.162 --> 43:07.444
(quietly): You must be crazy.

43:07.496 --> 43:09.196
- You tryin' to get us killed.
- MOSES: The Lord saw fit

43:09.248 --> 43:10.831
to show you mercy after you was

43:10.866 --> 43:12.499
dragged back here, and now you talkin'

43:12.535 --> 43:14.118
- like this.
- I wasn't tryin' to run.

43:14.120 --> 43:16.370
I was just tryin' to get into the city.

43:16.422 --> 43:19.373
Find a connection to the freedom train.

43:19.425 --> 43:21.508
All right, I need you
to tell me what this say.

43:21.544 --> 43:23.377
Now I know you crazy.
Massa see you with somethin'

43:23.429 --> 43:25.462
with words on it,
he gonna have your back peeled.

43:25.464 --> 43:27.431
I don't know who told you's
I could read,

43:27.466 --> 43:28.849
but they's mistaken.

43:28.884 --> 43:32.970
I thought God ain't take kindly
to tellin' lies.

43:32.972 --> 43:35.306
(grunts)

43:35.358 --> 43:38.309
I ain't gonna tell nobody.
Now, this is the map to freedom.

43:38.361 --> 43:41.312
I'm trustin' you with it.
You got to trust me, too.

43:41.364 --> 43:43.647
Okay, we all got to trust
each other. This whole thing,

43:43.649 --> 43:44.732
it don't work no other way.

43:44.784 --> 43:46.150
Oh, no. It don't work any which way.

43:46.202 --> 43:48.819
That's what they want you to
think, but we do this right,

43:48.821 --> 43:53.490
we do this together,
we can stand as free men.

43:56.662 --> 43:58.796
Ugly death.

44:00.666 --> 44:04.301
That's the only thing
we gonna find we stay here.

44:04.337 --> 44:06.420
S-Slip it to me.

44:06.472 --> 44:09.056
I see what it say back at my cabin.

44:11.510 --> 44:13.644
TOM: <i>You're not doing much talking</i>

44:13.679 --> 44:15.354
tonight.

44:16.515 --> 44:19.183
Having a hard time
opening up a conversation

44:19.185 --> 44:20.768
with your fellow slave owners.

44:20.820 --> 44:23.320
Well, it's all the more reason I
appreciate you making the trip.

44:23.356 --> 44:26.106
Mary's birthday isn't
a matter of politics.

44:26.158 --> 44:27.908
It's a matter of family.

44:27.943 --> 44:29.777
I, uh, couldn't help but notice
you and the wife

44:29.829 --> 44:31.174
weren't doing much talking either.

44:32.288 --> 44:34.031
You ever say something so reprehensible

44:34.083 --> 44:36.116
that you can't possibly take it back?

44:36.923 --> 44:40.120
Why do you think I own
so many acres of land?

44:40.172 --> 44:43.207
More places to hide. (chuckles)

44:43.209 --> 44:44.925
I love that accent
you've adopted, by the way.

44:44.960 --> 44:46.827
(chuckles) Mmm. Mm-hmm.

44:47.851 --> 44:50.097
I'm just trying to embrace the culture.

44:50.132 --> 44:52.766
Is that part of it? The bid for senator?

44:52.802 --> 44:54.218
Show 'em that you're one of them?

44:54.270 --> 44:55.686
They know I ain't one of 'em.

44:55.721 --> 44:57.021
That's why the Democrats approached me.

44:57.056 --> 44:59.448
They think I can speak
the language of the North.

45:00.496 --> 45:02.145
I hope I still can.

45:02.561 --> 45:04.028
Who's your campaign manager?

45:04.063 --> 45:06.113
- Smartest guy I know.
- Good. What's his name?

45:06.148 --> 45:08.148
John Hawkes.

45:09.819 --> 45:12.870
- (indistinct chatter)
- (chuckles)

45:12.905 --> 45:15.539
You have outdone yourself
tonight, Suzanna.

45:15.574 --> 45:17.491
They're gonna be talking about this one

45:17.543 --> 45:20.160
- for the rest of the year.
- It's not a competition.

45:20.212 --> 45:24.415
Says the woman who always wins.
(chuckling)

45:24.417 --> 45:27.751
Elizabeth, tell us about
the weather up north.

45:27.803 --> 45:30.313
Do y'all get anything like this heat?

45:31.608 --> 45:32.589
Elizabeth.

45:33.255 --> 45:36.760
Bernadette was asking
about the weather up north.

45:36.812 --> 45:39.396
Right. Um, yeah,
it d... it does get hot.

45:39.432 --> 45:40.731
But nothing like this.

45:40.766 --> 45:43.489
It's a bit, um... oppressive.

45:45.154 --> 45:48.439
Is your husband a planter
like his brother?

45:48.441 --> 45:51.442
No, no. John operates
a law practice in the city.

45:51.444 --> 45:53.327
He's also quite the activist.

45:53.362 --> 45:56.029
- Oh, that's wonderful.
- For what cause?

45:56.082 --> 45:57.781
Rights for niggers.

45:58.625 --> 46:01.838
I try not to talk politics
at social occasions.

46:01.890 --> 46:03.587
That's amusing, because I feel

46:03.622 --> 46:05.873
like all you Northerners do is talk.

46:05.925 --> 46:07.841
We're the ones down here
doing all the work

46:07.877 --> 46:09.460
to keep the economy going.

46:09.512 --> 46:11.295
(Elizabeth laughs softly)

46:11.347 --> 46:13.630
This cake is delicious.

46:13.632 --> 46:16.049
Did you make it yourself?

46:17.574 --> 46:21.138
I guess it's easy to be a woman
of ideals, given your...

46:21.173 --> 46:22.573
condition.

46:22.608 --> 46:24.808
And I promise you this.

46:24.810 --> 46:26.894
You and John will both
feel differently on the matter

46:26.946 --> 46:27.945
if you ever

46:27.980 --> 46:30.364
- have children.
- Now, I simply

46:30.399 --> 46:33.117
must show you ladies
where the nursery will be.

46:33.152 --> 46:35.569
Come. This way.

46:41.660 --> 46:44.661
(indistinct chatter)

46:54.507 --> 46:56.673
(owl hooting)

46:57.510 --> 47:00.894
(exhales)

47:00.930 --> 47:03.063
(sniffles)

47:05.851 --> 47:07.985
(exhales)

47:10.239 --> 47:12.356
(sniffles)

47:19.281 --> 47:21.281
That was-was real good of you

47:21.333 --> 47:23.813
to take them lashes for your brother.

47:28.424 --> 47:30.664
You says we all pretendin'.

47:32.959 --> 47:34.456
What'd you mean?

47:35.798 --> 47:39.132
We's all know we supposed to be free.

47:40.686 --> 47:45.431
I ain't been more than two steps
off this plantation in my life.

47:46.141 --> 47:49.047
Can't even imagine
what being free would be like.

47:51.780 --> 47:55.672
All them cities up north, they
all built of iron and steel.

47:56.285 --> 47:58.869
A free man, say with the skills I got,

47:58.904 --> 48:01.384
oh, he could live like a king.

48:02.374 --> 48:05.087
Go anywhere his heart desires.

48:05.494 --> 48:08.441
Live a life is his own
and no one else's.

48:08.831 --> 48:11.081
Except his wife, when he finds her.

48:12.251 --> 48:14.064
And they children?

48:14.837 --> 48:17.472
They ain't never gonna have
to think about runnin'.

48:25.931 --> 48:28.065
(footsteps approaching)

48:43.532 --> 48:46.617
Did you have a chance
to taste the peacock?

48:46.669 --> 48:48.035
(chuckles)

48:48.087 --> 48:50.037
No, I have had a scotch in my hand

48:50.089 --> 48:53.257
since we stepped off the stagecoach.

48:55.044 --> 48:58.519
I didn't drink nearly enough
to forget what I said to you.

48:59.131 --> 49:00.514
You're right.

49:00.549 --> 49:03.598
I need to start putting
our family first.

49:09.441 --> 49:12.286
Tom asked me to manage his campaign.

49:14.313 --> 49:16.647
If I want to make a difference,
a real one,

49:16.699 --> 49:20.076
then having the ears
of a senator could help.

49:20.903 --> 49:23.029
We'd have to move down here.

49:23.989 --> 49:27.422
But I'd be home more and
we'd be surrounded by family

49:28.789 --> 49:30.360
for when we have our own.

49:39.838 --> 49:41.897
It's me.

49:43.142 --> 49:46.265
I'm the reason that we
can't have children.

49:49.231 --> 49:50.229
Oh.

49:51.850 --> 49:56.269
They had a little boy up in a swing,

49:56.322 --> 49:59.523
and he was... fanning us in the parlor

49:59.525 --> 50:02.242
like he was just another
piece of the furniture.

50:02.745 --> 50:05.306
And no one cared.

50:11.086 --> 50:12.498
This...

50:13.835 --> 50:15.005
this isn't the kind of world

50:15.040 --> 50:17.371
that I want to bring children into.

50:21.046 --> 50:23.003
We have to change that.

50:26.146 --> 50:28.769
That's five dollars
from the Macon plantation.

50:28.804 --> 50:31.271
And here's $50 for the one
from Alabama way.

50:31.306 --> 50:32.389
Hold on now.

50:32.391 --> 50:34.891
The notice says $100, dead or alive.

50:34.893 --> 50:35.942
That's for the pair.

50:35.978 --> 50:38.445
- Male and female.
- That bitch?

50:38.480 --> 50:39.896
We done chased her over a cliff.
She fell.

50:39.898 --> 50:41.398
Must've been 50 feet.

50:41.450 --> 50:42.616
- Is that so?
- I reckon

50:42.651 --> 50:43.900
it could've been 75.

50:43.952 --> 50:45.619
Ain't no way to get that body.

50:45.654 --> 50:47.988
(chuckles) Well, the good Lord must
have been looking out for her,

50:48.040 --> 50:50.957
'cause she ended up in here
without a scratch on her.

50:50.993 --> 50:53.076
Rest of this money goes
to the slave catcher

50:53.078 --> 50:55.912
- who brought her in.
- JIM: And who's that, exactly?

50:55.914 --> 50:58.278
That'd be me, Jim.

50:59.501 --> 51:01.918
JIM: You stole her right from under us.

51:01.970 --> 51:03.804
CONSTABLE: Y'all ain't
the only ones tricked.

51:03.839 --> 51:06.590
He walked her right in here
with his coat over her head.

51:06.642 --> 51:08.892
I swear I heard her call him a saint.

51:08.927 --> 51:10.127
That true?

51:11.013 --> 51:12.814
Not at all.

51:13.399 --> 51:15.710
She called me an angel.

51:16.435 --> 51:19.352
♪ But if you do decide that you
gonna play that hand and try ♪

51:19.405 --> 51:21.271
♪ Just think before you act
because your actions

51:21.323 --> 51:23.106
♪ Don't rewind. ♪

51:24.443 --> 51:26.610
Hey, boy.

51:28.447 --> 51:32.082
Mr. Macon wants to see you
up at the big house. Now.

51:43.524 --> 51:44.845
We left off

51:44.880 --> 51:47.514
John 15:13. I got somethin' else

51:47.549 --> 51:49.287
I want you to read me tonight.

51:52.805 --> 51:54.261
Where'd you get this?

51:54.263 --> 51:55.605
Noah.

51:55.641 --> 51:57.641
He think I'm the one that can read.

51:57.693 --> 51:59.294
It's a song.

52:00.764 --> 52:03.936
My mama used to sing it to me
when I was no older than Boo.

52:05.289 --> 52:07.038
Some of the words are different.

52:07.569 --> 52:11.135
Yeah. Noah reckons
that that's the way to freedom.

52:13.759 --> 52:16.106
Sing it to me, Ma.

52:19.865 --> 52:22.919
♪ I've seen death ♪

52:23.502 --> 52:26.336
♪ But the moss stays the same ♪

52:26.338 --> 52:30.507
♪ The sun is shinin' ♪

52:30.509 --> 52:33.527
♪ Through the blue haze ♪

52:34.346 --> 52:37.597
♪ The drinking gourd ♪

52:37.649 --> 52:40.462
♪ The wolf yells its name ♪

52:40.769 --> 52:44.437
♪ The devil grins ♪

52:44.490 --> 52:48.024
♪ When he shows you the grave ♪

52:48.076 --> 52:51.194
♪ The River Jordan ♪

52:51.246 --> 52:54.531
♪ Rises on high ♪

52:54.566 --> 52:58.251
- (bell jingling)
- ♪ Pulls you closer ♪

52:58.287 --> 53:01.705
♪ To the angel's light ♪

53:01.757 --> 53:04.758
♪ And if you fall ♪

53:04.793 --> 53:09.129
♪ Get back up again ♪

53:09.181 --> 53:12.516
♪ 'Cause freedom's fruit ♪

53:12.551 --> 53:15.936
♪ Heals all your sin ♪

53:15.971 --> 53:19.389
♪ Waiting to see ♪

53:19.391 --> 53:23.560
♪ Heaven's door. ♪

53:23.562 --> 53:27.364
(door opens)

53:27.399 --> 53:29.533
(door closes)

53:33.038 --> 53:35.564
Y'all wait here.

53:39.578 --> 53:41.711
This can go one of two ways.

53:41.747 --> 53:43.830
I tell the massa
where I found your wagon.

53:43.882 --> 53:45.799
We see if that slick tongue
of yours can talk yourself out

53:45.834 --> 53:47.000
of a hangin'. You don't know nothin'.

53:47.052 --> 53:48.919
I know enough to know
you plannin' something.

53:48.971 --> 53:51.555
See, I think you runnin' and you
gonna take that boy with you.

53:51.590 --> 53:54.257
The way I sees you's watchin'
everybody, talking in hushes,

53:54.309 --> 53:56.593
maybe you gonna take some others, too.

53:56.645 --> 53:58.395
A thing you ain't consider,

53:58.430 --> 54:00.430
you get caught or not, it's gonna be

54:00.482 --> 54:02.599
the slaves left behind
that's gonna pay the price.

54:02.651 --> 54:04.651
Don't act like you care
'bout nobody else.

54:04.686 --> 54:06.202
You only care about yourself.

54:06.238 --> 54:07.437
You right.

54:07.439 --> 54:10.106
That's why I don't mean
to be left behind.

54:13.862 --> 54:16.196
Ain't no chance in hell.

54:16.248 --> 54:18.615
Let's go.

54:18.667 --> 54:20.667
♪ ♪

54:20.702 --> 54:24.704
Guess we gonna find out
who the big nigger is now.

54:24.756 --> 54:27.557
(rhythmic panting)

54:27.593 --> 54:31.011
It's been a long day.
What couldn't wait?

54:31.046 --> 54:33.463
Well, massa, we just wanted
to say we found your wagon.

54:33.515 --> 54:34.881
(rhythmic panting)

54:34.933 --> 54:36.800
You did?

54:36.852 --> 54:39.436
Good. Where was it?

54:39.471 --> 54:42.272
